The proposed solution introduces a decoupled communication layer but risks adding latency and complexity. While separating communication from optimization is a valid step, the design must prioritize lightweight, low-latency mechanisms (e.g., edge computing, prioritized message queues) to avoid new bottlenecks. The core issue—token-based prioritization—requires either smarter token allocation algorithms or a shift to non-token-based prioritization models (e.g., reputation-based or workload-aware systems).  
</text>
